<SubSection title="Thin-Walled Pressure Vessels" id="thin-walled-pressure-vessels">
<Itemize>
	<Item>Inner radius: <InlineEquation equation="r" /></Item>
	<Item>Wall thickness: <InlineEquation equation="t" /></Item>
	<Item>Thin walls: <InlineEquation equation="\\dfrac{t}{r} <<1" /></Item>
	<Item>Assume that stress distribution through the thin wall is uniform</Item>
	<Item>Pressure vessel contains fluid under pressure (<InlineEquation equation="p" />), usually called gauge pressure (i.e., <InlineEquation equation="p = \\Delta p = p_i - p_o" />).</Item>
</Itemize>
